main event: Two satellite-like objects with red and white flashing lights were reportedly observed in the sky near Wooster, Ohio.
interesting points: The sighting lasted for 45 minutes.,The objects were described as having red and white flashing lights.,The report suggested the objects could have been balloons or other astronomical phenomena.,The objects were observed at about 300 feet elevation.,The information was deemed inconclusive and data insufficient for definite evaluation.
sighted object: two satellite-like objects with flashing lights
witness description: Call from Flight Service reporting witness accounts of a red object traveling at high speed.
